reviews_data.review_text: Best Rhino location for sure. Chris in the Kitchen is the best there is, keep it up!

I have been coming here for years at all locations. I moved away to Texas and this was my first place I wanted to come to get a breakfast burrito while in town. When I went to pay they have the audacity to ask for a 50% minimum tip!! I'll be back but can guarantee that there will no be 0 tip left. Pay your employees more and don't ask me for it.

Rhino Market is the perfect combination of a classic deli and a local market. The sandwiches are yummy, with a variety of options (including vegetarian). Plus, the market offers a great selection of local items. Definitely a neighborhood favorite!
Had a gluten free sandwich and it was so good. Spoke to Will and he showed me the packaging for the gf bread. Great experience, will go back
Cool spot, never know if your sandwich is gonna take 5 minutes or 50 minutes. Wouldn't recommend if you ever need reliability.
Service is terrible at this place. I've gone in too many times with a smile and a friendly hello to only be greeted by disgruntled employees who seems unbothered and irritated by your service.

Jay and Will are the absolute best people I have ever had the pleasure of dealing with. They are a perfect representation of rhino market and all they have to offer. Thank you for the 2 best banging sandwiches I've ever had.
Ordered a cold turkey on sourdough add bacon, put some salt n pepper chips on it, 11/10 sandwich. Shoutout to the boi Will behind the counter preppin it up real nice

Will took great care of me and i genuinely had one of the best vegetarian sandwiches I've had in a long time. Never really didn't expect the sandwich to be that good. I had the portobello sandwich and would highly recommend.
Cool eclectic vibe. Lots of local options to purchase. Great place!

Holy mackerel! Came here on a Sunday afternoon and Will in the kitchen was splendid and the soup was delicious  I will definitely come back to this location in the future. Customer service and dedication to quality food is top priority here.
Rhino Market is a gem in the neighborhood. Huge shout out to Will in the kitchen - he has the best customer service! Staff is always friendly and food is always great.
Obsessed with this place. Major shoutout to Will for his great energy and service!
Good sandwiches and fast service

Where have I been the last ten years....under a rock? I've begun to patronize Rhinos only in 2024.Wow, I love this restaurant . There's a Rhino on every side of Charlotte. The food is exceptionally delicious . The employees are friendly and inviting. Yes, you will see me quite often. A definite recom
mend to my friends.

I stopped into the Rhino Market & Deli prior to checkin at the Courtyard as my room wasn't yet ready . I satisfied my hunger with a bacon egg & cheese on an everything bagel and root beer soda. While the store overall has a health conscious element to it, thankfully the not so healthy options are still available. There's a small sitting area and counter should you choose to dine in

Unika B. & Co.
It's a community staple and a great source of delicious food and beer
The egg salad sandwich is the best egg salad I've ever had- the carmelized onions take it past normal  boring egg salad, and sourdough bread is a good choice for it

Incapable of providing sandwich as ordered. 4th sandwi h in a row that's incorrect. Avoid

Edit: It happened in NoDa. And I am editing this review as it happened AGAIN today sat 13th December. Poor customer service at the Deli window, staff look annoyed that your looking to purchase food and their lack of enthusiasm leads to constant mistakes.

It has been too many times, I have asked asked for vegan sausage/soysage only to be given pork. There is no excuse as to why this should be happening. People have diet restrictions and it should be taken seriously

I love this setup! I imagine this is similar to a NYC bodega. You can browse the isles for interesting finds like honey Sriracha chips, grab a hot coffee, or order a sandwich (hot and cold) from the deli. You can also find local baked goods.
I ordered the "Stacked High". Pictures say it all - very disappointing $10 sandwich. Certainly was not "stacked high."

Love this place, minus the food. We have been here 3 times for food and each time it's been a letdown. We ordered the Big Wheel and it was a desert dry dune sandwich, with two pickles, on pumpernickel, honestly toasting the bread would be an improvement. The "deli" is always a disappointment.

Food was good, but deli staff so rude. No smile. No words spoken even after I said hello. Just stared at me until I said my order. Wrote it down on a ticket and handed to me. Again no words spoken. I felt like I was bothering her simply by ordering. And this was my first time here. And then register asks if I want to tip? Audacious. Lots of competition in the area, so no need for me to return.
Great vibe. Good beer selection and nice deli sandwiches.
I asked for a sub. I told him exactly what I went on the sub and I did not get what I asked for first time there and the last time.

I want so badly to like this place but they mess up my sandwiches every single time... today I got a BLT that had no tomato... the environment is cool and the staff are friendly though

Reply to owner - this is about the NoDa location

The service was pretty good.  But my primary reason was to get a good sandwich. Got the chicken salad sandwich and all that was in it was ground chicken lettuce and tomatoes.  With a few sparse droppings of celery.  No salt & pepper.  No mayo.  No love.  I was really looking forward to it and I was so disappointed that I left this review.

I went to the Noda location the food was ok wouldn't go again I got a Sicilian they only put cheese on one side of the bread and they didn't add mayo I asked for no peppers or tomatoes there were peppers and it was super vinegar heavy
Great food and service really enjoyed the breakfast Sean crafted.
Food is consistently good!

The food was great however, I was pretty disappointed with the service here in the NoDa location. I came here twice and it was almost as if I were bothering everyone for asking a question. The atmosphere was picturesque yet the employees made it uninviting. Good food but not worth the experience at all. Won't be there again.

This Rhino is not as good as the main location on Morehead, but I would choose it over the one uptown. It is usually lacking in space. Right now, the construction around the building makes it hard to access easily. The food is usually pretty greasy, but when it isn't, it's very tasty.

I had a ABLT-avocado, bacon lettuce tomato there this evening. It was a disappointment. One and a half slices of tomato one piece of lettuce. There was a good amount of bacon surprisingly and slight avocado. The sandwich might have been an inch in thickness if that tell you something. Will not eat there again.

Super disappointed in my first visit today. It was just after 11am on a Friday and I was a few minutes away. I went to order a salad on Rhino Market's website through GrubHub. There was an error with the ordering system (it required me to choose an extra dressing for a fee, which I didn't need/want) so I decided to just order in person. When I got in, there was no one else ordering or waiting. I placed my order, which the girl taking the order didn't seem familiar with. She didn't write my complete order on the ticket. I had to offer what dressing I'd like. While waiting for my pollo salad with chicken salad on top, I perused the aisles. Super cute local products as well as kitchen staples and snacks for sale. A large beer selection. I picked a couple of things and paid, then waited for my food. My salad took twenty minutes to be ready, and when it was ready it was missing the chicken salad. Just a plain salad, 20 mins wait on a Friday morning. Although I can't figure out the wait time, I honestly don't believe the missing chicken salad was the cooking staff's fault, because the ticket was incomplete. He graciously apologized and fixed it for me.

It wasn't until I got back to my vehicle and viewed my receipt that I decided to write this review.

**DO NOT ORDER THROUGH GRUBHUB from Rhino Deli unless you are prepared to pay an additional undisclosed 55% markup on the food here.** I was blown away when I realized I paid $8.99 for a salad that was $13.63 before fees and taxes to order online. I find this to be a shady business practice and believe it should at the very least be disclosed conspicuously on the business's website. While they may pay a fee to use GrubHub, a 56% markup per item is absolutely ridiculous.

The salad and chicken salad were just okay.

I love to give small local businesses my money, and I work a few blocks away. I'll never be back.
Alot to take in..
Great place for a quick snack or a bottled or canned beverage, especially if you're coming through off the Funny Bus tour.

Great food, great experience!
I enjoyed the portabello mushroom sandwich, all the veggies were fresh and crisp. The staff was super friendly as well. I will be back to try more of your delicious sandwiches!
Pit stop for the Charlotte Funny Bus tour.
Food is amazing and the selection of basically anything you could want is amazing!
Cute little market shop! Their sandwiches are great too. I love the ABLT!
Pit stopped while on bus tour. Classic convenience store pricing, but staff was friendly and knew the bus's routine
One of the best markets in Charlotte!  Great little bar, excellent food and wine to go, and the most friendly kitchen staff that makes the best sandwiches!!

The kitchen sink was clearly out of soap and paper towels - not sure how employees wash their hands. Further, a kitchen employee sagged so much his entire lower half was exposed - which is concerning from a sanitary perspective. Food was solid, but it's not worth getting sick over.
Really cool store. Must check it out if in Charlotte
The perfect market you never knew existed. Wanna drink? They got it. Need hangover help? They got it. Munchies? Go here and you won't have em.
Delicious food, awesome atmosphere, super friendly & helpful staff! I got a salad  from here recently that was excellent, will be back soon!
Wanted to get something to eat here but order window was closed they said to switch from breakfast to lunch. Oh well. Market seemed well stocked. Will try again soon.

Great place. Seating inside or outside. Plenty of beers on tap or cans. Bottles of wine that they will open for you to enjoy at your table. Coffee, tea, and all kinds of drinks. Order sandwiches or salads which were quite delicious. They also have breakfast.
I literally go to Rhino at least once a week. Great place!  I always get the portobello on the spinach wrap.
I absolutely love this place! It's like a hidden gem. I always get the vegan burrito and it hits the spot to my hunger satisfaction every time! Keep up the good work!
Tuesday night trivia was a blast what an awesome event! Great people. Will definitely be back.  Beer specials also.
My go to place for breakfast. Their breakfast burrito speaks to your soul in the mornings.
Rhino's Deli was a fantastic place to pop by and eat some sandwiches. Great environment and wonderful employees! Especially our chef Nico! I will be back!
Guys in the deli are great! The shrimp & crab gumbo is bombbbb.
Always great service! I order breakfast here at least once a week, and it's fresh every time!
Great food and coffee selections. Shout out to Walt up front and Niqo in the kitchen. This place has become a staple in the neighborhood.

Charlotte is so lucky to have Rhino. Best breakfast burrito in town, especially when my guy Nico is staffing the kitchen. I get em once a week.

Rob started something special years ago with the first location, but the Noda location remains my favorite. Walt, Hannah, Josh... the best.

Great spot in NoDa. The staff are friendly and welcoming. I get breakfast from here at least 2-3x a week. The Le Monde is my go-to; healthy spinach and tomato on toasted sourdough with havarti cheese. Also try the Pepperbox Nitro Latte when you need a caffeine boost!

They have a great beer and wine selection too!

So glad I stumbled across this place. Now, I come here every other day to work... it's such a great vibe. The staff are always welcoming. And the food... OMG!!! Always so good! I, especially, enjoy seeing the manager-- Nico I think? in the kitchen because he cooks my food like somebody's grandma!!! Lol Overall, if you're looking for a good atmosphere to work, have a professional meeting, or just a quick bite to eat, Rhino's at NODA is the perfect place.

Update: this place still can't make a bagel with cream cheese. Get new management and staff.

Place has gone down hill fast. I hope they get new management that can bare minimum teach a kitchen how to prepare a bagel and cream cheese. 9 out of every 10 times I get food from here there's something questionable about it. -Noda location
Great "work from home" location!

Ordered a vegan breakfast burrito which is supposed to come with a flour tortilla, potatoes, vegan sausage & cheese, salsa and spring mix and it came looking like this, on a wheat tortilla. I called and asked if they could remake it and said no because they stopped serving breakfast and all they could do was offer me a refund. If an order is made incorrectly you'd think they could just quickly make it for you. Super disappointed because I eat here multiple times weekly.
First time there and will go back no problem prices are high but you are paying for some really great food nice cozy spot
I just went in for a quick bite to eat and was surprised at the beer on tap, and very nice selection of bottles "to go".
One of the best sandwich shops in the Queen City. The Rueben is choice
The staff here is rude af and the food is subpar at best. This place has definitely declined significantly in quality and service.
Good subs!

If I could give zero stars I definitely would. I walk into the store and, was never greeted but they greeted everyone who came in after me. I was the only person of color (customer)in the store. The sign that they have hanging in there says we give excellent service. So I order,go to the register and, people were just standing and I waited for the last person I saw and, I went to register to pay. Well the rude white man told me with a frown on his face that there's a line. I didn't know line's were formed in between the isles so I get in line and the white man is frowning his face discussing me. How unprofessional is this business. I pay go to the back to get my food and, I'm standing there waiting for my food. All the time your non greeting person just looked at me and, talking with coworkers. After about 10 minutes of looking at me she finally told me that my food was in another window. Took one bite and, totally disgusted me. I will never return to this evidently doesn't want people of color in their establishment.
Stopped in to grab a breakfast sandwich and some snacks. Good service and good food. No complaints!
Chicken torta #FTW
THESE GUYS ROCK!
Very cool place with tons of options for food, drinks, and snacks!
Nice convenience store.  Big beer selection.
Cute little market with lots of choices of unique items and great beer selection. Go when the deli is open though for great sandwiches.
Spent time in NYC and love delis. This place rocks! Got the Hot Roast Beef ($8) and it was delicious. Will be back for the Wednesday special soon.

I ordered a Rhino Club on ciabatta (extra .$99 charge for ciabatta) and got a sandwich on over-toasted sour dough bread. The Rhino Club menu item states "dijon vin" as an ingredient on their large posted menu board. The kitchen team used dijon mustard instead of dijon vin. I politely asked for my sandwich to be remade due to my distaste for dijon mustard and the chef was more interested in telling me that "dijon vin" and dijon mustard are the same thing instead of helping me. I didn't care about the over pay for wrong bread and I had all the time in the world to wait for a new sandwich made to menu specifications but I had zero time to argue with someone about the difference between "dijon vin" and dijon mustard.

Please fix menu listing on the large board you have posted or please fix the build of sandwich in the kitchen.

Please be kind.

The Thursday Special was the worst sandwich I've ever had in my entire life, and this is no exaggeration.

That being said, everything else I've had here has been fine, if not a bit over-priced.
First time here and somehow they get a build your own sandwich wrong? Who forgets cheese and puts mustard when I asked for no mustard? Would drive back for a refund if I wasn't so annoyed.
The service  and the deli are great! But their healthy food options has definitely gone down in the past months, I don't think I be coming back as often unless that change
Rhino is my favorite place in Charlotte for breakfast. Their ruben and chicken torta are awesome for lunch.
Their breakfast burrito is the best.
Great place to find craft beer
I'm a regular at Rhino Market. I go every day for coffee, and often a breakfast or lunch sandwich. Best place in Charlotte!
Great breakfast sandwiches!! still buying, still great 2/26/22

*DO not support this business*
They pay their kitchen workers poverty wages (14-15.00 per hour). Find a more ethical place to eat....

Dont go on weekend morning!Probably my 10th visit... today not a good day.  I know they are short staffed but deli was backed up.   I purposely ordered what I thought would be a easy item, a muffin with egg, havarti and sausage.  My number was 24...  after 20 min, they were calling numbers after mine, large orders, 5-6 items.  After 30 min they were calling numbers in the 30's. I asked deli staff and was told "it's on its way.  We are 20 min behind. " well after 40 minutes  "number 24".  I went outside to eat with my now empty coffee cup.  Muffin had no sausage.
Disappointed.

Great little market/deli with a bar (beer and wine) where you can get fresh made breakfast, sandwiches, and salads.

I got the chicken torta after getting a pedicure next door. It was really good but the chicken pieces were so big that big chunks of chicken came out every bite I took. It was pretty messy to eat!

The parking is weird but they have a decent number of spots that they share with the other businesses in the building.
Very good restaurant good food

Two words: breakfast burritos.

But I'm all seriousness, this is a Charlotte staple and each neighborhood boasts its own vibe. Go on and check them out!

The pastrami sandwich is really good 
Piled high!!
Great place for sandwiches and local goods.
Nice place with hipster vibe, good coffee, and allows dogs! Staff was cheerful and helpful, and I will be back.
They have vegan options!!!
Cool spot.  Good food.  Great coffee
Freshest bread I've ever had

I'm here at least once a week. Who cares about the stars, I'm voting with my dollars. Even though I can only give this spot five stars, it's got everything worth your dollars. I call that everything the Spinach and Bacon Salad with balsamic vinaigrette. And a Swedish Fish of course. They sell them by the singles. Because that's a thing apparently. I'm glad it is.

We love Rhino Market, but we visited today and even though the front of the store has a sign indicating masks are required they are allowing people to walk around without masks. Down the road, the bodega and breweries are enforcing,  but Rhino Market is not.
Grab a beer or sandwich here. Great staff
This place has my new life hack for coffee: nitro cold brew vanilla oat milk latte. It's on tap(!), it's fast, and it's delicious.
My only complaint is that the pork sandwich is only available on Thursdays.
Never disappoints! Breakfast burrito, lunch Sammies, snacks, beers, desserts, vegan options....they have it all! And staff is always super friendly.
Who doesn't like a good Deli sandwich?
Great food - chicken torta is really good! Love the vibe of the place. Great place to do work/study
This place is amazing! Fantastic selection of brews, Food is pretty righteous,  and staff and customer service is 10 out of 10!!!
Love their sandwiches!
Great place, for all food orders you need to head to back of location once inside building
Awesome place
Great breakfast. Price, taste, and speed are all superlative for CLT
Bunch of different beers and wine and snacks.... We stopped here as a halfway point on the funny bus

Wish they kept stock of the vegan options on the regular. Changes often and hit or miss. Staff is super friendly which helps. Breakfast burritos are yummy . I do the vegetarian version. If everything was 1.00 cheaper it would be a 5 star

Great place for a bite to eat or a drink. They have a plethora of beers, wine, and more to browse and take to go or drink on site as well as a number of beer on draft. I tried the food for the first time recently and it did not dissapoint. It's a deli style menu with sandwiches and salads with many vegetarian options

One of my favorite places to pick up quick bite.  Their freshly made sandwiches are awesome.  Their breakfast burrito is awesome too.  Fun place to hang out with a pint or wine (they sell it all here).  Fun place to get some work done or read a book while grabbing some lunch and a drink.  Staff is always welcoming and helpful.  I have been here dozens of time, and will continue to return.  I like shopping here for unique food & beverage items that are hard to find in traditional stores. Go give them a try...
Tasty sandwich!

I've only been to the local Rhino Market & Deli location in NoDa a few times, but each time leaves me wanting to make it a regular stop. This is the kind of place that made living in NoDa a solid choice. They have a wealth of local products of all kinds, and Rhino whips up some serious sandwiches. Use my pictures as proof, and do yourself a favor by stopping by. Act like a PRO the first time by hitting the back area where the condiments are and be sure to add some extra greatness to your sandwich if consuming it in-house (or grab packets to go).
Cool place. And they've got delta 8!!

Great customer service!  If you don't see something on the menu to order, you'll probably find a prepared version. From healthy drinks to beer/wine, you can find what you want. Love the variety and options available.

My seven year old son walk into the establishment his mask was not pulled up completely on his nose this man stops what he is doing and ask him could he pull up his mask there was also a young White female in her early 20 he said nothing to I felt so offended I left out I will be reaching out to any outlets I can to make them aware of this behavior it is not ok
Great customer service
Nice spot to get a snack on the go. Great sandwiches.
A hidden gem near noda
Great beer selection, iffy service
Awesome market in NoDa!! They have a great selection of foods and snacks, and an even larger stash of great wines and beers.
Incredible place! Love the people, awesome deli, and so happy they're here in NoDa!

I was treated well the first
Time I went inside . The food
Is all ways good
Only reason it's even getting any stars is cause the deli isn't that bad but customer service at all rhino market locations is piss poor
The guy making the food here had a mask but it was bellow his nose and mouth. It wasn't just to take a breath either. Talking to coworkers and prepping all with no mask. Eeek
Mandi (at the bar) was very friendly and helpful.  Great atmosphere for a quick lunch escape from the office!  Good spacing between tables and patio options as well.  Will definitely be back soon!
Incredibly bland sandwiches but they have a super d beer selection
Great beer and sandwiches.  Breakfast burrito is amazing.
Watched the people in the kitchen preparing multiple food orders with no mask
Nice deli and market. Breakfast sandwiches were good, coffee is good but options are limited. Bagel was amazing.
Decent but overpriced breakfast sandwich, pretty good beer selection but the worst coffee I've ever had in my entire life.
Best sandies in town.
Excellent roast beef!!

I used to work at the pool right down the street so I would always stop by for a snack and a sandwich if I didn't bring my lunch. They have such a wide variety of drinks, candy, snacks, and fresh foods. Everything is fairly priced. My only with is that there was more parking.
Try the Chicken Torta sandwich it's DELISH! Definitely a cool spot to grab a drink/meal

Was at the NODA location today and the customer service was very unwelcoming. Everyone had an attitude and was even told to bring in my dirty cups from outside before I even had a chance to eat. Not happy. The food was good, however.
Horrible customer service. Unfortunately Oh My Soul was closed. I suggest going there instead. (NODA location)
Amazing selection and the sandwiches are amazing!
Similar to a classic bodega, with good food at a decent price. Also a suprising amount of alcohol.
Customer service not pleasant. Sandwiches are good
I enjoy their many beer choices
Great choice of beers and a nice easy going atmosphere!
Amazing breakfast ....a little pricey
Love the spinach bacon salad
Walked in dolly Parton was playins so I automatically loved the place. Food was.good too
cool place with a unique and eclectic selection of drinks snacks and goods in general. great little deli that makes fresh and delicious sandwiches. vegetable soup is bomb

Rhino Market is a safe bet for good sandwiches and a great selection of beverages, both alcoholic and non-alcoholic. They also have two aisles of snacks (sweet and salty) and several local and non-local beers on tap as well as Prosecco and wine by the glas. It's a great addition to the NoDa/Villa Heights area, as we were missing a good sandwich shop. The staff is always super nice and they are part of the bicycle discount places across town. Buy a sticker for $5 from any location (Birdsong is also part of this program) and you get discounts whenever you ride your bike to these places and show your helmet with the sticker on it.

I especially love their sandwiches and that they have gluten free bread that I can pair with their vegan sandwiches. We've never had a bad experience at Rhino Market. The vibe is relaxed and I love their patio on a sunny day. Definitely a highlight in the NoDa/Villa Heights area!
Awesome sandwiches, this place is great. Love the Italian. Great selection of beers chips and many other things.
Nice convenience shop with beer and deli. What more can you ask for? Sandwich was excellent accompanied by a draft beer and chips

Great atmosphere, beer, wine, coffee, and food. But even without all of these things, I would still come here regularly to hang out and work due to the killer music they always seem to be playing. Never thought I would hear The Pharcyde and The Cocteau Twins in the same place! One of my Charlotte favorites.
Awesome breakfast burritos. Love the grill in the back, great simple food and fairly priced.
Bfast burritos, A-okay!
Great neighborhood place for sandwiches, snacks, beer, wine, etc... or just for hanging out.
This deli is awesome! The staff is always friendly and the food is quick and cooked to order!
Delicious sandwich.  Nice atmosphere.
Great friendly service

This is one of my favorite local markets to stop by and get some work done for a few hours. The space is always clean, there is plenty of space to sit, and the snack options are endless! I recently had the "soup of the day" special - curry soup, and it was delicious and hearty! They also have quite a few brews on draft and tons of cans and bottle options to take home. Indoor and outdoor seating, great music and friendly staff - what more could you ask for?

There area several of these places spattered across Charlotte.  So when you go to the Rhino Market & Deli you get a hip cafe, bar and smaller grocery store.  This concept can be found in a lot of places across the country at the moment.  The closest place in Charlotte that you could compare it to would be the Common Market.

Ordered a Sicilian (hot) was skeptical but it was a really good sandwich.  I'm from out of town so had no knowledge of this place but happy I gave it a shot.  Relatively fast service and friendly staff 5/5 stars.  If you've never tried their sandwiches it's worth grabbing one.
The breakfast bagel was delish and quickly prepared. Coffee is also very good. Like the "help yourself" atmosphere. Nice outside seating.
Has just about anything you could want out of a local hot spot. Lunch was fresh and yummy.
Great food, awesome beer selection
Great sandwiches salads & service

This location is the least appealing out of all the rhino markets. Zero character which is a let down for noda. The food is sub par, lacking design and ingredients, it's all rather bland. The atmosphere is horrid, the lights are too bright, not enough seating and the bar takes up most of the building so the space you have to order a sand which, pick up said sandwhich and shop for snacks gets very congested and stressful. The vibe is very stale, little to no personality from the bartender or the guys making your food, I don't feel wanted when I walk into the door and because of that I will take my sandwich dollars elsewhere.

I eat here at least once a week.
The staff are very friendly as well
Going to see Honey Bear spin tunes Aug 17th 8 - 10 and Aug 19th 1 - 3pm!

Awesome market/deli. Friendly staff and great environment! The food was fast and very good. Beer selection from the coolers was great and the bar itself was very well stocked. Awesome selection of unique chips and other items. I will definitely be returning! It is great to have this in Villa Heights!
Great place to go and hang out. Love the deck area here.
Nice variety of wine, healthy snacks, hot food and beer with a relaxed environment.

Wish I could say I like this place better than I do. On paper I should. But it's just a bit too stuffy for my taste. The food was actually pretty decent. I tried the Hot Roast Beef which had a satisfying horseradish taste. But the vibe and customer service was a little dry. Not to mention seating and space was really crowded when we went. Employees (at least the ones I interacted with) were surface level friendly which kind of made me feel like they were sale focused instead of building relationships. Not really my scene but your mileage may vary.

Great Lunch!!! Sandwich selection serves meat eaters & vegetarians. Fresh bread and veggies cooked to perfection on sandwich. Curry soup was Delicious! Pasta salad was yummie :) Will def return as staff was helpful & place was very clean. Thank you Rhino Market!!!
Best breakfast burrito in town!

Very similar to the Plaza Midwood Common market. Craft beers and lunch specials. They also serve breakfast. Very friendly staff and they give very good recommendations. Nice relaxing space, very well placed seating.
Service left a lot to be desired, uninviting atmosphere and nothing more than edible food

Wonderful selection of beer, wine, food snacks, light fare. Nice crowd, seating inside and out. Staff friendly, accommodating, and attentive. Music a little loud for conversation, however when asked to have it a little more quiet there was a quick response to accommodate. Great place to gather with friends!
Charlotte's best Deli
Omg so good. Came in to kill time and got some food while I waited. The Chicken Torta soooo delish! I need this sandwich everyday. Everyone in the store was super friendly and helpful!

a wonderful addition to our neighborhood. grab a bottle of wine, and a bite to eat.
and trivia every Tuesday  at 730p
Finally a deli in Charlotte that reminds of the ones up north. To me, this is what a deli is supposed to be. Every sandwich I've had has been great! You guys rock! Thanks for coming to Noda!
Love this location. Great sandwiches and beer selection. Nice staff and lovely atmosphere. Also love that it's right next to Free Range brewery, one of my favourites in Charlotte.
Great food!!!!

I've been to the other Rhino Markets and this is my favorite. Like the other locations you can't go wrong with the deli- both vegetarian and non-vegetarian. Great place to have a beer or take one home.
Love that Rhino Market is in Noda! Great food and a nice atmosphere! I've been two days in a row. Are three too many?
Such a great addition to the NODA neighborhood, their sandwiches are fuego and their beer selection is amazing. I will definitely be a regular :)!

Love the new place here in NoDa where we can ride our bikes to and have a beer. Super nice people and great new hang out. Can't wait to try every delicious item on the menu. We will definitely be here a lot going forward.
